HEADWORD: Dancett
<hw>Dan`cet`t⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>danch⟦eacute⟧</ets> dancett⟦eacute⟧, <ets>dent</ets> tooth.]</ety>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Deeply indented; having large teeth; thus, a fess
<xex>dancett⟦eacute⟧</xex> has only three teeth in the whole width of
the escutcheon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

